+# Meta Note - Step 003 Exploration 003
+
+## What Worked
+
+- Treating the tidy second-budget pictures as pseudo-survivors only for the
+  purpose of an admissible-enlargement test kept the step honest while still
+  explaining why Chain Step 3 is unearned.
+- Re-adding the first forced orbit before rerunning closure showed that both
+  pseudo-survivors fail for the same reason as the raw closure audit:
+  pruning the first spill mode was doing all the apparent stabilizing work.
+
+## Reusable Lesson
+
+- When no honest survivor remains, the enlargement pass should stress-test the
+  most tempting over-pruned picture rather than pretend a true survivor exists.
+
+## Caution
+
+- A clean second-budget negative still does not authorize mission-level
+  termination or self-escalation to the next rung.
