+  mirror/parallelogram subfamily.
+- Ran a direct coefficient probe on representative geometries with all seed
+  sign assignments using
+  `explorations/exploration-002/code/shared_mode_closure_audit.py`.
+
+## Outcome
+
+`succeeded`
+
+## One Key Takeaway
+
+No honest second-budget seed survives.
+The generic five-orbit fan spills when cross-triad pairs force a new target on
+`a+b+c`
+or its first sign-variant companions, and the mirror/parallelogram family
+spills when
+`(a+b,b)`
+or
+`(a-b,-b)`
+forces
+`a+2b`
+or
+`a-2b`.
+In the representative audit, all `32/32` live seed sign assignments in each
+family forced at least one new target sector.
+
+## Leads Worth Pursuing
+
+- Treat Chain Step 3 as unearned on this budget unless an enlargement audit can
+  somehow rescue one of the pseudo-survivor pictures.
+- Use the first forced new orbit from each family as the explicit enlargement
+  test in the verdict pass.
