 # History of Report Summaries
 
 Exploration summaries will be appended here as they land.
+
+## Exploration 001 Summary
+
+- Goal:
+  classify the canonical second-budget seed families for two-triad shared-mode
+  clusters.
+- Outcome:
+  `succeeded`.
+- Takeaway:
+  `[INFERRED]` the honest second-budget catalog has two genuinely new geometric
+  seed families:
+  the generic five-orbit shared-mode fan
+  `{ (a,b,a+b), (a,c,a+c) }`
+  and the four-orbit mirror / parallelogram subfamily
+  `{ (a,b,a+b), (a,-b,a-b) }`.
+  Any two-triad picture contained entirely in the old mirror-complete one-triad
+  support is only a disguised first-budget dead seed.
+
+## Exploration 002 Summary
+
+- Goal:
+  run the recursive exact closure audit on each canonical second-budget seed.
+- Outcome:
+  `succeeded`.
+- Takeaway:
+  `[INFERRED]` no honest second-budget seed survives.
+  The generic fan spills when cross-triad pairs force
+  `a+b+c`
+  or its first sign-variant companions, and the mirror/parallelogram family
+  spills when
+  `a+2b`
+  or
+  `a-2b`
+  is forced.
+  In the representative Step-3 audit, all `32/32` live seed sign assignments
+  in each family forced at least one new target sector.
+
+## Exploration 003 Summary
+
+- Goal:
+  run the admissible-enlargement audit on any apparent second-budget survivor,
+  or package a clean current-budget negative if none remain.
+- Outcome:
+  `succeeded`.
+- Takeaway:
+  `[INFERRED]` the enlargement audit confirms the negative.
+  Restoring the first forced orbit to the generic fan opens targets like
+  `a+2b+c`
+  and
+  `a+b+2c`,
+  while restoring
+  `a+2b`
+  to the mirror/parallelogram cluster opens targets like
+  `a+3b`
+  and
+  `2b`.
+  No genuinely invariant finite support survives the second budget, and Chain
+  Step 3 remains unearned.
