+# Exploration 003 Summary
+
+## Goal
+
+Run the required admissible-enlargement audit on any apparent second-budget
+survivor, or package a clean current-budget negative if none remain.
+
+## What I Tried
+
+- Treated the generic five-orbit fan and the four-orbit mirror/parallelogram
+  cluster as pseudo-survivors only in the sense needed for an enlargement
+  stress test.
+- Added the first closure-forced orbit from each family and reran the closure
+  logic conceptually from scratch.
+
+## Outcome
+
+`succeeded`
+
+## One Key Takeaway
+
+The enlargement audit confirms the negative.
+Restoring the first forced orbit to the generic fan immediately opens targets
+like
+`a+2b+c`
+and
+`a+b+2c`,
+while restoring
+`a+2b`
+to the mirror/parallelogram cluster opens targets like
+`a+3b`
+and
+`2b`.
+No genuinely invariant finite support survives the second budget, so Chain
+Step 3 is still unearned.
+
+## Leads Worth Pursuing
+
+- Hand controller a second-budget obstruction memo rather than a Step-3
+  dynamics handoff.
+- If controller escalates later, start the next rung explicitly from the
+  smallest three-triad repeated-wavevector-across-scales budget rather than
+  recycling any two-triad pseudo-survivor.
